      "content": "In a rough, industrial neighborhood where outsiders are wary, a realistic suspect might be someone who fits the local profile—likely a long-time resident or someone who has managed to blend in despite not being born there. They might be a part of the community, maybe even a small-time criminal or a struggling worker who feels justified in their actions due to economic hardships. Look for someone with a history of strained relationships with law enforcement, someone who knows the area well, and perhaps a few tattoos or a shabby appearance that suggests they’ve lived on the streets. This person might also have connections to local gangs or underground networks that operate in the shadows.",
